    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><date>Wednesday, 13 Tebeth, (February), 1865</date>.</p>
            <p>Greetings to <sic>myfriend</sic> and the friend of the Most High:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I sent you four sheets of manuscript but there has been no<lb/>
                answer. Today, I am sending you 22 sheets. I beg you for a quick re-<lb/>turn of
                them. My conjecture about the Samaritans is found in the <hi rend="underline"
                    >Ba'al</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">'Akeda</hi>, but without proof.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am very much surprised not to find my article about the<lb/>
                seminary nor the one about the Spaniards in the “Occident”. I was<lb/> right that
                    <persName>Illoway</persName><add>?</add>, as some one told me today, has a great
                deal of<lb/> conflict in <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>. His reports were pure
                inventions. <persName>Szold</persName> is<lb/> the same kind of sloppy fellow, whom
                the false mi...... [sic] permitted to<lb/> come there for his barmitzvah.... This
                    <persName>Szold</persName> knows neither Hebrew<lb/> nor German....... Shall I
                report to <placeName>Pittsburgh</placeName> ? I shall.... and<lb/> ask why I did not
                go to <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>. If you have acquaintances there,<lb/>
                write to me about it... Unfortunately, my wife is sick. I am very confused (upset) my<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline"><persName>Esther</persName></hi> takes up much of my time.</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">With respect,</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Your very devoted,</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Jonah Bondi</persName>
            </p>
            <p>In the <hi rend="underline"><placeName>Jeshurun</placeName></hi> I am in the company
                of <persName>Luzzato</persName>, better than<lb/>
                <persName>Szold</persName>, <persName>Wise</persName> and
                    <persName>Illoway</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="(The original letter is in very bad shape)"/>
            <pb n="Card"/>
            <p><persName>Mr. H. Nathan</persName>.</p>
            <p>
                <placeName>29-South 2nd St</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
